{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantTypeRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"[Type","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":"] types are represented as strings, but have a strict","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"syntax described below. All [type"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantType","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"]s passed to GLib must be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"valid, and they are typically expected to be static (i.e. not provided by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"user input) as they determine how binary [type"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":"] data is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interpreted."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To convert a static string to a [type"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantType","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] in C, use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.VARIANT_TYPE"},{"text":"] casting macro. When GLib is compiled with checks","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"enabled, it will validate the type. To check if an arbitrary string is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"valid [type","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantType","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"], use [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.VariantType.string_is_valid"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"GVariant Type System","level":2,"anchor":"GVariant-Type-System"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This section introduces the [type","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"text":"] type system. It is based, in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"large part, on the D-Bus type system, with two major changes and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"some minor lifting of restrictions. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"http:\/\/dbus.freedesktop.org\/doc\/dbus-specification.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"therefore, provides a significant amount of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"information that is useful when working with [type"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first major change with respect to the D-Bus type system is the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"introduction of maybe (or ‘nullable’) types.  Any type in [type","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can be converted to a maybe type, in which case, ","type":"text"},{"code":"nothing","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"null"},{"type":"text","text":")"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"becomes a valid value.  Maybe types have been added by introducing the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"character "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"m"},{"text":" to type strings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The second major change is that the [type","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] type system supports"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the concept of ‘indefinite types’ — types that are less specific than"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the normal types found in D-Bus.  For example, it is possible to speak"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of ‘an array of any type’ in [type"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"], where the D-Bus type system"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"would require you to speak of ‘an array of integers’ or ‘an array of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"strings’.  Indefinite types have been added by introducing the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"characters "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"*"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"?","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"r"},{"type":"text","text":" to type strings."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally, all arbitrary restrictions relating to the complexity of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"types are lifted along with the restriction that dictionary entries","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"may only appear nested inside of arrays.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Just as in D-Bus, [type"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":"] types are described with strings (‘type"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strings’).  Subject to the differences mentioned above, these strings","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are of the same form as those found in D-Bus.  Note, however: D-Bus","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"always works in terms of messages and therefore individual type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strings appear nowhere in its interface.  Instead, ‘signatures’"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are a concatenation of the strings of the type of each argument in a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"message.  [type","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"text":"] deals with single values directly so","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[type"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":"] type strings always describe the type of exactly one","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value.  This means that a D-Bus signature string is generally not a valid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[type","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] type string — except in the case that it is the signature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a message containing exactly one argument."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An indefinite type is similar in spirit to what may be called an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"abstract type in other type systems.  No value can exist that has an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"indefinite type as its type, but values can exist that have types","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that are subtypes of indefinite types.  That is to say,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Variant.get_type"},{"type":"text","text":"] will never return an indefinite type, but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calling [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Variant.is_of_type"},{"text":"] with an indefinite type may return","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"true.  For example, you cannot have a value that represents ‘an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"array of no particular type’, but you can have an ‘array of integers’"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which certainly matches the type of ‘an array of no particular type’,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"since ‘array of integers’ is a subtype of ‘array of no particular"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type’.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is similar to how instances of abstract classes may not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"directly exist in other type systems, but instances of their"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-abstract subtypes may.  For example, in GTK, no object that has"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the type of "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/gtk4\/class.Widget.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"exist (since "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkWidget"},{"text":" is an abstract class), but a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/gtk4\/class.Window.html"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can certainly be instantiated, and you would say that a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkWindow"},{"type":"text","text":" is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkWidget"},{"type":"text","text":" (since "},{"code":"GtkWindow","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a subclass of "},{"code":"GtkWidget","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two types may not be compared by value; use [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.VariantType.equal"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.VariantType.is_subtype_of"},{"text":"]  May be copied using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.VariantType.copy"},{"text":"] and freed using [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.VariantType.free"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"GVariant Type Strings","level":2,"anchor":"GVariant-Type-Strings"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A [type"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"text":"] type string can be any of the following:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"any basic type string (listed below)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"v","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"r","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"one of the characters ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"a"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"m"},{"text":", followed by another type string","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the character "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"("},{"text":", followed by a concatenation of zero or more other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type strings, followed by the character ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"the character ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{"},{"text":", followed by a basic type string (see below),","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"followed by another type string, followed by the character "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"}"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A basic type string describes a basic type (as per"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.VariantType.is_basic","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]) and is always a single character in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"length. The valid basic type strings are ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"n"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"q"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"i"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"t","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"h","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"o"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"?"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The above definition is recursive to arbitrary depth. ","type":"text"},{"code":"aaaaai","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"(","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"ui(nq((y)"},{"code":"))s)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are both valid type strings, as is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"a(aa(ui)`(qna{`ya(yd)`}))`. In order to not hit memory limits, [type"},{"text":"Variant``] imposes a limit on recursion depth of 65 nested","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"containers. This is the limit in the D-Bus specification (64) plus one to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allow a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/class.DBusMessage.html","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to be nested in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a top-level tuple."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The meaning of each of the characters is as follows:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_BOOLEAN"},{"type":"text","text":"; a boolean value."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_BYTE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; a byte.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"n"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_INT16","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"; a signed 16 bit integer."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"q"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT16"},{"text":"; an unsigned 16 bit integer.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"i"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_INT32"},{"type":"text","text":"; a signed 32 bit integer."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT32","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; an unsigned 32 bit integer.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_INT64"},{"type":"text","text":"; a signed 64 bit integer."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"t"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT64"},{"text":"; an unsigned 64 bit integer.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_HANDLE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; a signed 32 bit value","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that, by convention, is used as an index into an array of file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"descriptors that are sent alongside a D-Bus message.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_DOUBLE"},{"text":"; a double precision","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"floating point value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_STRING"},{"text":"; a string.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"o","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_OBJECT_PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; a string in the form","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a D-Bus object path."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_SIGNATURE"},{"text":"; a string in the form of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a D-Bus type signature.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"?","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_BASIC","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"; an indefinite type that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is a supertype of any of the basic types."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"v"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; a container type that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contain any other type of value."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"a","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": used as a prefix on another type string to mean an array of that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"type; the type string "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ai"},{"type":"text","text":", for example, is the type of an array of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"signed 32-bit integers.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"m"},{"type":"text","text":": used as a prefix on another type string to mean a ‘maybe’, or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"‘nullable’, version of that type; the type string ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ms"},{"type":"text","text":", for example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is the type of a value that maybe contains a string, or maybe contains","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"nothing."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": used to enclose zero or more other concatenated type strings to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"create a tuple type; the type string ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(is)"},{"text":", for example, is the type of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a pair of an integer and a string."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"r","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the type string of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_TUPLE"},{"text":"; an indefinite type that is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a supertype of any tuple type, regardless of the number of items.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"{}","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": used to enclose a basic type string concatenated with another type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"string to create a dictionary entry type, which usually appears inside of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an array to form a dictionary; the type string ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"a{sd}"},{"text":", for example, is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the type of a dictionary that maps strings to double precision floating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"point values."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The first type (the basic type) is the key type and the second type is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the value type. The reason that the first type is restricted to being a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"basic type is so that it can easily be hashed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the type string of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_ANY"},{"text":"; the indefinite type that is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a supertype of all types.  Note that, as with all type strings, this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"character represents exactly one type. It cannot be used inside of tuples"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to mean ‘any number of items’."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any type string of a container that contains an indefinite type is,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"itself, an indefinite type. For example, the type string "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"a*"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(corresponding to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_ARRAY"},{"text":") is an indefinite type","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that is a supertype of every array type. ","type":"text"},{"code":"(*s)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a supertype","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of all tuples that contain exactly two items where the second"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"item is a string.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"a{?*}","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an indefinite type that is a supertype of all arrays"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"containing dictionary entries where the key is any basic type and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the value is any type at all.  This is, by definition, a dictionary,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"so this type string corresponds to "},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_DICTIONARY","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Note"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that, due to the restriction that the key of a dictionary entry must"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be a basic type, "},{"code":"{**}","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not a valid type string."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantTypeRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVariantType"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","typ